//                              Comments
// Block style comments begin with /* and terminat with */ that spans multiple lines.
// Line style comments begin with // and terminate at the end of line.
// Documentations style comments begin with /** and terminat with */ that spans multiple lines.
// They are generlly created using the automat documentation generation tool such as java.
//                              Conversion	
// Every expression written in the java programming language has a type that can be deduced from the structure of the expression and the type of the literals,variables, and method mentioned in the expression.
//                              Widening conversion
// int y=3;
// float x=y;  no error
//                              Narrowing conversion
// float x=3.4f;
// int y=x; error
// int y=(int)x;  no error
// float k=3.5; error
float k=3.5f; no error

//                              Permitted Conversions
// byte to short,int,long,float, or double
// short to int,long,float, or double
// char to int,long,float, or double
// int to long,float, or double
// long to float or double
// float to double
